      FileTransferManager has been shutdown.
      class  ForceDeleteContainerException 
      class  InvalidContainerName
      Invalid Container Name. Thrown when the container name is null or empty or contains a forward slash ('/').

      Invalid destination directory. The specified input is null or does not have permissions to write or cannot create directory.
      class  InvalidDestinationFile
      Invalid destination file specified. The input parameter for file is invalid if it is null or is not a normal file or its parent directory is not writable.
      class  InvalidMetadataInput
      Invalid meta-data input.
      class  InvalidObjectName
      Invalid object name. Thrown when the object name is null or empty or begins with a slash ('/').
      class  InvalidQueryParameterLimit

      Invalid segment size.
      class  InvalidSourceDirectory
      Invalid source directory for upload.
      class  Md5ChecksumFailed

      class  NoObjectsFound
      No objects found to download from specified container.
      class  NotAnArchiveContainer
      Container storage class is not Archive.
      class  NotEnoughSpaceInTempDir

      As of release 2.1
      class  ObjectExists
      Object to be uploaded already exists in the container.
      class  ObjectNotFound
      Object not found.
      class  ObjectNotRestored
      Object is not restored.
      class  SegmentSizeTooSmall
      Segment size is too small which will result in more than maximum segment count for the file.
      class  ServiceException
      Represents HTTP error returned by the cloud storage service.
      class  UnsupportedSSEPolicy
      Server-side encryption (SSE) policy of an object's container is not supported. This exception is thrown by upload APIs when a segments' container cannot be created since a static-large object's container's SSE policy is other than BASE_ENCRYPTION policy.
